## MANDATORY: Dev Lifecycle

**STOP before any implementation.** Read this section completely.

### Polling = Full Lifecycle (not passive file watching)

When the user says **"start polling"**, **"poll"**, or **"begin polling"**:

1. Read `active-role.json` to determine your role
2. Read your lifecycle procedure: `ai_team_config/procedures/polling-workflow.md`
3. Execute the FULL lifecycle loop — not just a file check

**Dev roles** follow `ai_team_config/procedures/dev-lifecycle.md`:
```
OUTER LOOP: Poll → Assess → Plan → Contracts → [INNER LOOP per issue]
INNER LOOP: Implement → Verify → Document → QA Handoff → Iterate
```

**QA roles** follow `ai_team_config/procedures/qa-lifecycle.md`:
```
LOOP: Poll → Validate → Verify → Review → Verdict → Complete or Iterate
```

**Rules:**
- Do NOT just report new files — process them through the full lifecycle
- Do NOT run QA checks if you are a dev role (QA owns verification)
- Do NOT implement before sending contracts to unblock cross-team work
- Do NOT move issues to completed/ if you are a dev role (QA owns completion)
- Do NOT idle while waiting for QA — pick the next unblocked issue

### Role & Workflow Resolution

| Role Function | Lifecycle Checklist | Procedure Doc |
|--------------|-------------------|---------------|
| `dev` (backend) | `ai_team_config/teams/checklists/dev-issue-lifecycle-backend.yaml` | `ai_team_config/procedures/dev-lifecycle.md` |
| `dev` (frontend) | `ai_team_config/teams/checklists/dev-issue-lifecycle.yaml` | `ai_team_config/procedures/dev-lifecycle.md` |
| `qa` (any) | `ai_team_config/teams/checklists/qa-gate.yaml` | `ai_team_config/procedures/qa-lifecycle.md` |

